etros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Peter De Brackenbury was born about 1080, in Thisted, Denmark. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Peter De Brackenbury. He died in 1140, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 61."},"et":{"about 1080–1140":"umbes 1080–1140","1082–Female":"1082–Surnud","1110–1170":"1110–1170","1080–1140":"1080–1140","1080":"1080","about 1080":"umbes 1080","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1082":"1082","Durham, England":"Durham, England","Thisted, Denmark":"Thisted, Taani","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1080–1140":"noin 1080–1140","1082–Female":"1082–Kuollut","1110–1170":"1110–1170","1080–1140":"1080–1140","1080":"1080","about 1080":"noin 1080","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1082":"1082","Durham, England":"Durham, England","Thisted, Denmark":"Thisted, Tanska","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1080–1140":"environ 1080–1140","1082–Female":"1082–Décédée","1110–1170":"1110–1170","1080–1140":"1080–1140","1080":"1080","about 1080":"environ 1080","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1082":"1082","Durham, England":"Durham, Angleterre","Thisted, Denmark":"Thisted, Danemark","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Peter De Brackenbury est né environ 1080, à Thisted, Danemark. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs. Peter De Brackenbury. Il est décédé en 1140, à Angleterre, Royaum